DIAG_ENTRY(WarnUnnecessaryVirtualSpecifier /* unnecessary-virtual-specifier */, 22236, /* DiagArray1025 */ 2906, 0, R"(Warns when a ``final`` class contains a virtual method (including virtual
destructors). Since ``final`` classes cannot be subclassed, their methods
cannot be overridden, and hence the ``virtual`` specifier is useless.

